emuInput.TitMainTitle: Dancer Chuck Fly standing in between the Crosley sisters, in interior
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1955, pg. 18, reads: "The Fly Performs - Dancer-mimic Chuck Fly strikes a pose with the Crosley sister with whom he shared the bill at the Vogue Terrace through Oct. 2. Personable Chuck will perform his dancing feats next in Detroit where he was signed for a two-week engagement. - Harris Photo."
